..TEXT:
Bunyan, ^Pilgrim's Progress~: -- "But now in this
valley of Humiliation poor Christian was hard put to it; for he
had gone but a little way before he spied a foul fiend coming
over the field to meet him; his name is Apollyon.  Then did
Christian begin to be afraid, and to cast in his mind whether to
go back or stand his ground. ...Now at the end of this valley was
another, called the valley of the Shadow of Death; and Christian
must needs go through it, because the way to the Celestial City
lay through the midst of it."
