..TEXT:
Dante as a Ghibelline and Imperialist is in
opposition to the Guelfs, Pope Boniface VIII., and the King of
France, Philip the Fair, and is banished from Florence, out of
the sunshine, and into "the dry wind that blows from dolorous
poverty."
..TEXT:
Cato speaks of the "silent moon" in ^De Re Rustica~,
XXIV., ^Evehito luna silenti~; and XL., ^Vites inseri luna
silenti.~  Also Pliny, XVI. 39, has ^Silens luna~; and Milton, in
^Samson Agonistes~, "Silent as the moon."
